                     <origDate notBefore="1890" notAfter="1970">Late 19th - 20th century (?). &#xD;
                        Despite the mention of Za-Manfas Qǝddus as the donor (the baptismal name of
                        <persName ref="PRS8265Sabagadi">daǧǧāzmāč Sabāgādis</persName>, 1770-1831) and the information in the colophon, the Ms.
                        is palaeographically datable only to a much posterior period, and is
                        probably a copy of a book which was indeed commissioned and donated by
                        Za-Manfas Qǝddus/ Subagadis.</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Za-Manfas Qǝddus and his mother Walatta Ṣǝyon
                     are mentioned in supplication formulas and in the colophon. Other persons
                     mentioned are Za-Manfas Qǝddus' son Walda Mikāʾel (e.g., <locus target="#42vc">42vc</locus>, <locus target="#44vbc">44vbc</locus>, <locus target="#50rb">50rb</locus>), his father Walda Lǝʿul and Walatta Śǝllāse
                     (e.g., <locus target="#36va">36va</locus>, 54ra, 85ra). All names were added in
                     a secondary hand.</provenance>
               </history>
